    - rid: 138986247837974613
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 2
        question:
        - "A planet has a mass of 6 x 10^24 kg and a radius of 6.4 x 10^6 m. Using
          G = 6.67 x 10^-11 N\xB7m\xB2/kg\xB2, which of the following is the planet's
          escape velocity?"
        - Calculate the escape velocity for a planet with a mass of 6 x 10^24 kg
          and radius 6.4 x 10^6 m. (Use G = 6.67x 10^-11). Which of the following
          is the planet's escape velocity?
        correctAnswer:
        - "1.12\xD710^4m/s"
        wrongAnswers:
        - "5.6\xD710^3m/s"
        - "2.5\xD710^4m/s"
        - "9.8\xD710^3m/s"
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974614
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - "Which of the following correctly states Newton\u2019s Law of Universal
          Gravitation?"
        - "Which of the following explains what Newton\u2019s Law of Gravitation
          says about mass and distance?"
        - "Which best describes Newton\u2019s Law of Universal Gravitation?"
        correctAnswer:
        - Objects with mass attract each other, and the force depends on mass and
          distance
        wrongAnswers:
        - Gravity only works on Earth and not in space
        - Only large planets can exert gravity
        - Gravity is always constant, no matter the mass or distance
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974615
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - Which describes the speed required to break free from gravity?
        - "Which of the following correctly defines \u201Cescape velocity\u201D?"
        correctAnswer:
        - "The minimum speed needed for an object to escape a planet\u2019s gravitational
          pull"
        wrongAnswers:
        - The speed at which gravity becomes zero
        - The maximum speed of sound in the atmosphere
        - The rotation speed of a planet
        choiceCount: 4
